{
  "$comment": "WorldBuild Bench model registry. Prices are USD per million tokens and must be re-verified before publishing each round.",
  "$comment_pricing": "Anthropic rows were checked against the official price sheet 2026-07-03. Direct Kimi rows were checked against official Moonshot pricing and model documentation 2026-07-20. Other non-Anthropic rows were checked against provider/OpenRouter listings 2026-07-03. OpenRouter routing prices can change; MiniMax M3 and Qwen3.7 Max currently carry promotional rates, Claude Sonnet 5 is intro-priced through 2026-08-31, and Gemini 3.1 Pro tiered pricing above 200K input tokens is not represented by this flat table.",
  "$comment_routing": "provider selects the adapter (anthropic | openai | google). The openai adapter also serves compatible endpoints such as Moonshot and OpenRouter. base_url_env overrides base_url when set; api_key_env names the credential variable but never contains the credential.",
  "$comment_output_caps": "max_output_tokens is the per-turn cap sent to the provider: the lesser of the documented model maximum and a 32768 practical ceiling for non-streaming requests. Anthropic rows use 16384 because direct requests that may exceed ten minutes require streaming. Reasoning tokens count against the cap where the provider bills them as output.",
  "$comment_cache": "Cached reads and writes use the published rates below. Anthropic reads are 0.1x input and five-minute writes are 1.25x; GPT-5.5 cached input is 10% of list; Gemini 3.1 Pro implicit-cache reads are $0.20/M. A provider-reported exact cost, when available, overrides this reference table.",
  "$comment_reasoning": "reasoning_effort is the generic CLI tier used for the run. reasoning_effort_map translates supported generic tiers to provider-native values; the direct Moonshot Kimi K3 route maps every accepted tier to its documented max setting. The selected generic tier is recorded in result.json.",
  "$comment_vision": "vision marks models that accept image input. Direct Moonshot Kimi rows, Anthropic rows, GPT-5.5, Gemini 3.1 Pro, and OpenRouter MiniMax M3 are enabled; GLM-5.2, Qwen3.7 Max, and DeepSeek V4 Pro are text-only. Vision models receive playtest screenshots, and result.json records whether images were sent.",
  "$comment_reasoning_effort_map": "Optional mapping from generic CLI tiers to provider-native effort values. Declaring a map restricts a model to the listed generic tiers. WorldBuild Bench runs Kimi K3 at max effort for consistent comparisons, so every accepted generic CLI tier maps to max.",
